---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Malik Danab - About Me"
  description="Malik Danab is a Gameplay Programmer and Technical Designer working in C#, C++, Unity, and Unreal Engine 5, with an ATEC degree from UT Dallas."
  active="about-me"
>
  <main class="page-modules">
    <h1 class="page-title">About Me</h1>
    <div class="text-block">
      <div>
        I'm Malik Danab, a Gameplay Programmer and Technical Designer who just finished my degree
        in Arts, Technology, and Emerging Communication (ATEC) at UT Dallas with a Concentration in
        Animation &amp; Game Design. I've been making games for 9 years now, starting with simple
        scripts and working my way up to full systems architecture, mostly in C#, C++, Unity, and
        UE5.
      </div>
      <div>
        I'm comfortable on both the design side and the code side of a game. On my solo project
        FourSight that meant building the simulation on Unity's ECS, and on the psychological
        horror game InVein it meant sound systems and rendering work. Either way, I want the
        mechanics I build to be stable and feel good to play.
      </div>
      <div>
        When I'm not in an IDE, I'm likely "researching game design" by playing Magic: The
        Gathering, Slay the Spire, or playing DND.
      </div>
      <div>
        <a href="/resume.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download my r&eacute;sum&eacute; (PDF)</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-block">
      <h2 class="title">Skills</h2>
      <div><strong>Languages:</strong> C#, C, Java, Python, HTML, Lua</div>
      <div>
        <strong>Engines &amp; Tools:</strong> Unreal Engine 5, Unity, GameMaker, Panda3D, Houdini,
        Git, Perforce, Maya, Rhino 5, Aseprite
      </div>
      <div><strong>Pipelines &amp; Ecosystems:</strong> .NET, SQL, Adobe Suite</div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
